{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix inconsistent default table selection in DL TDA info function\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_dl_tda_info` function in the NR MAC common module had inconsistent behavior when falling back to default time domain allocation tables. For certain RNTI types (C-RNTI, CS-RNTI, etc.), the function was hardcoded to use default table A regardless of the mux_pattern parameter, while other RNTI types correctly used the mux_pattern to select the appropriate default table (A, B, or C).\n\nThis inconsistency could lead to incorrect PDSCH time domain resource allocation when the network configures a specific multiplexing pattern but the UE falls back to default tables.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_COMMON/nr_mac_common.c`: Modified the `get_dl_tda_info` function to use `get_default_table_type(mux_pattern)` for all RNTI types when falling back to default tables, ensuring consistent behavior across all RNTI types.\n\n"
}